Package: UniversalShrink
Title: Regularized Pseudo-Inverse Estimation of High-Dimensional Covariance Matrices
    and Functions Thereof by Shrinkage 
Version: 0.0.0.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alexis", "Derumigny", , email = "a.f.f.derumigny@tudelft.nl", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6163-8097")),
    person("Nestor", "Parolya", , email = "N.Parolya@tudelft.nl", role = c("aut"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2147-2288")),
    person("Taras", "Bodnar", email = "taras.bodnar@liu.se", role = "aut", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7855-8221"))
	)
Description: Develops methods for regularized linear and nonlinear shrinkage 
   estimation of high-dimensional quantities such as the covariance matrix, 
   precision matrix and optimal portfolio weights, building on recent theoretical
   results by Bodnar and Parolya (2025, 2026) <doi:10.1090/tpms/1239>, 
   <doi:10.1214/25AOS2602>. These approaches stabilize sample-based estimators 
   by shrinking noisy eigenvalues of the sample covariance matrix and its 
   (pseudo-)inverses, including the standard inverse, Moore-Penrose inverse, 
   ridge inverse and Moore-Penrose-ridge (MPR) inverse, toward smoother targets.
   This improves numerical conditioning and enhances out-of-sample performance.
